gate-6 (cm-1 dual-rail) EXCLUSION — literal-NEWLINE argument (tc-gate6-multiline-argv). The
book has `apt-get install -y "multi<NL>line"` (a multiline string arg). The engine's
`--debug-argv` renders only the arg's FIRST line (`argv 0 replace apt-get install -y multi`),
but the slice-4 mock-log protocol encodes the WHOLE arg onto one line
(`ran: apt-get install -y multi\nline`). gate-6 attributes a bare-only elided line by matching
it against the ledger argv — truncated `… multi` never matches encoded `… multi\nline`, so the
converged elision false-fails as "unattributable". (Pre-slice-4 this false-PASSED by accident:
the un-encoded newline split the bare log, the first piece coincidentally equalling the
truncated ledger.) gate-5 + the exec gates still cover the case; only gate-6 opts out. The
value lives in the filename; this text is documentation.
